text: Nasser Al Omran (; born 13 July 1997) is a Saudi Arabian footballer who plays as a midfielder for Saudi Pro League side Al-Shabab . ==Career== Al Omran started his career at Al-Shabab and is a product of the Al-Shabab's youth system. On 1 March 2018, Al Omran made his professional debut for Al-Shabab against Al-Ittihad in the Pro League, replacing Turki Al-Ammar. On 2 July 2019, Al Omran signed a 4-year professional contract with Al-Shabab. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Saudi Arabian footballers Category:Association football midfielders Category:Saudi Professional League players Category:Al-Shabab FC (Riyadh) players Category:Saudi Arabia youth international footballers
